	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64370890"><p>Transactions per second. Its a measure of how fast it is based on a transaction, which is generally a single cycle of the bus</p><p>This is because the amount of data transferred per transaction can vary depending on whether you're using a x1 or x16 link. Sine the latter can do 16 times more data in a cycle than the former, using raw bandwidth is a bit useless.</p><p>So basically it's saying it can do 128GT/s. Each lane can do 1 bit in each direction per transaction, so a x1 will do 16GB/s (8GB/s up and 8GB/s down) in to<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64370890">

